<h2 id="#FleetManagement">Fleet Management</h2>
<h3>Overview</h3>
<p>
    Each player has two sets of fleet lists. One of these is the Home Fleet and the other is the Assault Fleet.
    These lists contain the units from which all other army lists are drawn.
    The Home Fleet is used for defensive army lists and the Assault fleet is used for offensive army lists.
    During a turn a unit on the army list may normally only be used once.
    This means that it may be possible that no valid army list can be made!
    Players are expected to create valid army lists whenever possible, and in cases where this is not possible they should make it as close to valid as they possibly can.
    If an invalid list is to be used, the opposing player should be informed and should approve the list to ensure that this approach is not abused (e.g., no lists where 80% of the list consists of dreadnoughts).
    When a defending player does not have sufficient points available to create a defensive list, he or she should draw units from the Assault fleet to create a valid army list.
    If all these steps have been taken and the defending player still does not have sufficient units available to defend, the defending player probably isn't long for this campaign anyway.
</p>
